node.text:
More than the launch of unparalleled works of jewelry craft, @Bulgari's Magnifica High Jewelry collection is a celebration of rebirth. Honored through magnificent muses, music, and Milan, take a look at Bvlgari's latest high jewelry collection.
 
Models: @vittoria, @lilyaldridge @heconghc, @solangesmith and @blesnyaminher
Special Guests: @andreabocelliofficial @beatricevenezi
Project by @oma.eu
Director @tommaso.ottomano
DOP@ mrcodepa
Stylist @sagliogeraldine
Music @guazzonemarco 
Production @studio.april
#Bvlgari #BvlgariJewelry #BvlgariHighJewelry #BvlgariMagnifica #Milan

node.text: After making her #NYFW modeling debut at @ProenzaSchouler, @EllaEmhoff landed a knitwear collaboration with Batsheva Hay (@batshevadress). The 21-year-old student, model, and designer met up with Hay amid NYFW—and #GoodMorningVogue was there to capture their conversations about materials, fit, and texture, plus Ella's rise to fame in the wake of the inauguration of President Joe Biden and Emhoff’s step-mother, Kamala Harris, in January.

node.text: This month, Vogue joined forces with an army of photographers and models all around the globe—stable Zoom connections required, please!—and sent the best and brightest of the new collections via courier services everywhere from Beijing to Brazil, Lagos to Los Angeles. Our concept? Simple, glorious movement: After a year of stasis, immobility and lockdowns, we wanted to see spring fashion breaking free. These are the looks we love, shot by the photographers we adore, on the run and out for a walk, a swim, a dance. Tap the link in our bio to see more.

node.text:
Today, @KamalaHarris became the first woman of color ever sworn in as vice president of the United States.

To celebrate this moment, twelve young women discussing what it means to them to see a Black woman of Indian descent elected to the second-highest office in the land. “Every little girl sees that this is a country of possibility,” @KamalaHarris states in one address, and that sentiment is widely echoed. “She reminds me every day that I am capable and worthy of my wildest dreams,” says one participant.

Director @rombokob
Producer @aliwebb_producer
Casting Director: Rebecca Dealy
Archival Research: Manon Blackman
Editor @ann_lupo
GFX @horatiobaltz
Color @carlosfloresfilms
Mix @cstropko
Post Production @forager.tv

node.title: 12 Girls on What Kamala Harris Becoming Vice President Means to Them

node.text: Throughout the political tumult of 2020, @janayathefuture was one of the most prominent voices to become a source of healing and hope. Reflecting on this week’s events, Khan points out the lack of police presence at the Capitol, a fact that exposes, in their own words, “a clear double standard for how Black protestors have been treated over the past several years. What we know to be true is that there is a way that white rage is celebrated in this country and Black grief is criminalized.” To hear more, make sure to check out Khan’s Sunday Sermons, returning tomorrow 1/10  at 12PM PST on their account.

node.title: @janayathefuture on Moving Forward from the Capitol Riots

node.text:
Daniel Arnold was on hand to shoot the 2021 #MetGala this Monday, and his intimate view of the event provides a glimpse at an array of famous faces that might just make you feel like you were there IRL. See Arnold's photos of "fashion's biggest night" at the link in our bio.
Photographed by @arnold_daniel

node.text:
@ShawnMendes and @camila_cabello were inspired by Studio 54 for the 2021 #MetGala. In two glamorous looks by @MichaelKors, they paid homage to the fabulous ensembles that were often seen by the hottest celebrities back in its heyday. In a new Vogue video, we got to see just how the couple got glam for their big night. Tap the link in our bio to get ready for the Met gala with the couple.
Director: @rombokob
DP: @raachelbatashvili
Cam Op: @brndnyn
Editor: @smurfyrose
Audio: @javier_caso
Audio: @thecarl10experience
Location: @rosewoodthecarlyle

@OliviaRodrigo made her #MetGala debut this year, adding to a huge year for the 18-year-old singer-songwriter. At the link in our bio, go behind the scenes with Olivia Rodrigo as she prepares for her first-ever Met gala red carpet.

node.text:
@KendallJenner was inspired by an American icon for the 2021 #MetGala: Audrey Hepburn. Designed by @Givenchy's Matthew M Williams, Jenner's look was modeled after a look Hepburn wore in the 1964 film My Fair Lady. “She wore Givenchy in almost all of her movies,” Jenner tells Vogue. “She’s the biggest legend; I’ve been obsessed with her my whole life.”

At the link in our bio, get ready with Kendall Jenner as she takes us behind the scenes for her night at the 2021 Met Gala.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Vogue on September 15, 2021 tagging @hunterabrams, @yarashahidi, and @dior. May be an image of 1 person and standing.

node.text:
Given that 2021’s #MetGala centers on the Costume Institute’s In America: A Lexicon of Fashion exhibition, @YaraShahidi wanted her look to honor the contributions of one of a true trailblazer: Josephine Baker.

“My goal was to pay homage to [a] powerhouse renegade black American artist,” shared Shahidi. Working with longtime stylist @JasonBolden and the team at @Dior, Shahidi set out to incorporate elements from Baker’s actual wardrobe into her gown. A committed history nerd, she and Bolden poured over imagery featuring the star. 

At the link in our bio, Shahidi gives Vogue a behind-the-scenes look at her #MetGala look and night. Photographed by @hunterabrams

node.text:
Just as thrilling as all the #MetGala night's most flamboyant looks was everything taking place behind the scenes. And for that, Vogue’s resident street style photographer Phil Oh (@mrstreetpeeper) was on hand to capture all of the action on the lead-up to the red carpet. Tap the link in our bio for a look at a side of the Met Gala we don’t usually see. 

Photographed by @mrstreetpeeper

node.text:
@EmmaChamberlain was going to do an updo for her first #MetGala but thought that it might look too, “going to my first prom.” 

The 20-year-old YouTube sensation has never actually been to the dance, since her vlogs began to take off when she was only 16. Instead, she has the Met. “Actually this kind of feels like going to prom, because of the nerves,” she says in her getting ready video. “You’re not that scared but you’re excited. This is my prom experience.”

From her glam conversations to her first time wearing her beautiful @LouisVuitton look, tap the link in our bio to watch an inside look at our red carpet host's very first Met gala.
